'''Reidi Artom''' was a [[Gender/Legends|female]] [[Near-Human]] [[Realspace/Legends|space]] explorer that discovered and named the [[Reidi Artom I system|Reidi Artom I]], [[Reidi Artom II system|Reidi Artom II]], [[Reidi Artom III system|Reidi Artom III]], [[Reidi Artom IV system|Reidi Artom IV]], and [[Reidi Artom V system]]s. Additionally, she rediscovered the [[Cularin system/Legends|Cularin system]] (initially Reidi Artom VI) in [[232 BBY/Legends|232 BBY]].<ref name="LFC" />

==Biography==
Reidi Artom belonged to a long-lived [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] [[Species/Legends|species]]. Her people generally stayed on their own [[Planet/Legends|planet]], something a young Artom did not understand. She loved excitement, adventure, and the thrill of exploration, so she escaped her [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] early in her life. For years, she wandered aimlessly, working whatever jobs would allow her to get from one place to another.<ref name="LFC" />

Artom gained her exploring vessel, the ''[[Trailblazer (Reidi Artom)|Trailblazer]]'', in a unique manner. After she stowed away on the [[Scout ship/Legends|scout vessel]], the [[Starship/Legends|ship]] came under attack. After the [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] was killed, nearly instantly, the ship was left floating in space. She made repairs and, after using the [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] to get to a [[Spaceport/Legends|starport]], [[Transponder code/Legends|registered]] the ship in her own name. In an effort to explore new [[Star system/Legends|systems]] and undiscovered space while getting paid for it, Reidi became a [[Scout/Legends|scout]] for the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]]. Although many scouts explored the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] or the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim]], Reidi surveyed the [[Exploration Region]] to find planets that had been overlooked. She was credited with the renewed interest that followed her explorations in at least eight systems.<ref name="LFC" />

During her first scouting in the Cularin system in 232 BBY, Artom visited the system from the outer to the inner planets. As such, she found the [[Almas Sith fortress]] in [[Almas]]; the [[Crystal Snare]] in the [[Cularin asteroid belt]], and the mysterious lava-like creature of [[Rennokk]] in her second visit to the [[Moon/Legends|moon]]. She also befriended the [[Tarasin]] native species of [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]] to the extent that she was taken to the [[Sacred ch'hala tree grove|Sacred Ch'hala Tree Grove]] &mdash; a honor that was bestowed to few outworlders since.<ref name="LFC" />

Artom spent nearly twenty-five years charting the Cularin system. She and her crew were credited with founding the settlement of [[Gadrin]] on Cularin. She was last seen heading off to explore the Unknown Regions in [[207 BBY]]. Due to the length of her people's lives, as of [[31 BBY/Legends|31 BBY]] it was believed that she could still possibly be alive and exploring.<ref name="LFC" />

Reidi Artom's impact was clear within the Cularin system, as time was measured on both [[Cularin/Legends|Cularin]] and [[Almas]] by the A.A. ("[[After Artom]]") time system. This time system measured its starting point at the discovery of the system.<ref name="LFC" />

A 60 meter-tall statue of Artom stood in front of a museum dedicated to her in Gadrin; the statue was visible from [[House Hirskaala]],<ref name="TRW">{{LivingForce|Eye of the Sun: The Resistance Within}}</ref> and was used for a medal ceremony organized by [[Governor/Legends|Governor]] [[Barnab Chistor]] of Gadrin in 31 BBY.<ref name="ARv">{{LivingForce|Eye of the Sun: Revelation and Refutation}}</ref>

[[Lavina Durada-Vashne Wren|Lavina Wren]], the Republic [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] for Cularin was rumored to be a distant descendant of Artom.<ref name="Cularin's Lady Senator, Lavina Wren">{{Wizards|url=rpga/livingforce/article.asp?x=lf/swlf20011206a_oblivion&c=swlfc|text=Cularin's Lady Senator, Lavina Wren}}</ref>

